Source: Calculated on the basis of the buying and selling rates of the following banks: Since December 2003 DNB, Oslo (formerly: DnB NOR) 1991 - November 2003 Den norske Bank, Oslo 1989 - 1990 Den norske Creditbank, Oslo

Comment on 1992-12-10: On 10 December 1992, the Norwegian central bank decided to abandon the unilateral peg-ging of the Norwegian krone to the ECU and allow the krone to float. On the basis of the ex-change rates on 9 and 11 December 1992, the krone depreciated by 6.5% against the US dollar (middle rate). No exchange rate data are available for 10 December 1992.
